    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce new requirements for businesses with air-conditioners/chilled units",
        "additional_details": "- all chilled units in grocery stores must have covering or doors to retain the refrigeration efficiently.\r\n\r\nI walk past many buildings where the door is open and the air-conditioned is blasting out, often at the open entrance. Air conditioners and electric fans have been found to consume around 10% of global electricity. They can leak hydrofluorocarbon refrigerants (HFCs), powerful planet-warming gases and a major contributor to global heating, into the atmosphere. The most commonly used \u2013 R-410A \u2013 is more than 2,000 times more potent than carbon dioxide.\r\n\r\nBy mandating closed doors for businesses with air-conditioning and protective coverings for refrigerated units, we can conserve electricity and curb harmful greenhouse gas emissions.",
        "background": "Make it law that:\r\n\r\n- shops/businesses that are running air-conditioning (whether for heating or cooling) must have doors that remain closed until opened by people entering/exiting.",
